{"tid":2308086,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"英美加日等18國155名議員聯署 促林鄭月娥確保12港人安全","createTime":"2020-12-01T15:15:28.000Z","updateTime":"2020-12-02T01:23:35.000Z","uid":240362,"like":59,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":35,"replies":[{"pid":"c75b6d438450fa5666afd3addf83bb8529d59ea6","tid":2308086,"uid":240362,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-01T15:15:28.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://scontent-hkt1-2.xx.fbcdn.net/v/t1.0-9/128661817_3421395877980861_8237171097765706287_o.jpg?_nc_cat=100&amp;ccb=2&amp;_nc_sid=8bfeb9&amp;_nc_ohc=EthXtnBEOegAX_sS3lx&amp;_nc_ht=scontent-hkt1-2.xx&amp;oh=67d6305b43ea1a85e9aee5bd9969d7b1&amp;oe=5FED5807\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fscontent-hkt1-2.xx.fbcdn.net%2Fv%2Ft1.0-9%2F128661817_3421395877980861_8237171097765706287_o.jpg%3F_nc_cat%3D100%26ccb%3D2%26_nc_sid%3D8bfeb9%26_nc_ohc%3DEthXtnBEOegAX_sS3lx%26_nc_ht%3Dscontent-hkt1-2.xx%26oh%3D67d6305b43ea1a85e9aee5bd9969d7b1%26oe%3D5FED5807&h=cd0ad697&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nHong Kong Watch<br />\n⛵️ 秘密監禁100天 &mdash;&mdash; 全球18國155位議員要求釋放 #12港人<br />\n<br />\n#12港人 至今被中國當局秘密監禁逾100天，全球155位來自美國、英國、加拿大、澳洲、日本、歐盟等18個國家的議員政要聯署去信林鄭月娥要求香港政府採取行動確保12港人安全並回應以下四項要求：<br />\n<br />\n1. 釋放12港人，送返香港受審；<br />\n2. 允許家屬委派的律師會見12人；<br />\n3. 允許12港人直接聯絡家屬；<br />\n4. 確保12港人得到需要的藥物及醫療支援。<br />\n<br />\n12港人歸期未有期，又未能直接與家屬及外界聯繫，真實情況不得而知。我們將繼續推動國際社會對中國政府施加壓力，要求釋放12港人；亦呼籲香港人繼續關注12港人，積極參與聲援活動，保持事件熱度。<br />\n<br />\n⛵️ 100 Days of Incommunicado Detention &mdash;&mdash; International Statement Demanding to #SAVE12<br />\n<br />\n#12Hkers have been held in incommunicado detention for over 100 days.<br />\n<br />\nIn response, 155 prominent politicians from 18 countries including the United States, the United Kingdom, Canada, Australia, Japan and the European Union have written to Chief Executive Carrie Lam, urging for the actions from the Hong Kong Government to satisfy the following demands,<br />\n<br />\n1. That the young people be returned immediately to Hong Kong. If they are to stand trial, they should be tried in the Hong Kong courts,<br />\n2. That the activists be allowed to nominate the legal representatives chosen by their families,<br />\n3. That the families of those arrested be allowed to contact them,<br />\n4. That the activists be allowed access to their prescribed medication.<br />\n<br />\nDate of #12Hkers&rsquo; return remains unclear. Without direct access to families and the outside world, the real situation of them is still unknown to us. Hong Kong Watch will continue to raise international awareness and pressure on the Chinese Government to release them, we also urge you to continue to pay close attention to their situation until we bring them home.<br />\n<br />\n✉️ 公開信內容 FULL STATEMENT<br />\n<br />\nDear Chief Executive,<br />\n<br />\nWe write to raise our concerns about the ongoing detention of twelve young people from Hong Kong in Shenzhen, and to ask that you use your position to raise their case with Chinese Communist Party officials in Beijing.<br />\n<br />\nThe reason that 2 million people Hong Kongers marched against the extradition bill in 2019 is because of their concerns about the mainland justice system where imprisonment is essentially guaranteed, torture is common and forced confessions are frequently demanded of suspects.<br />\nBasic decency and human rights must be considered in the case of these vulnerable young people. In your role as Chief Executive, it is incumbent on you to intercede on behalf of these young people to ensure that they are guaranteed justice.<br />\nTo continue to fail to do so would be a gross abdication of your responsibility to serve the people of Hong Kong and ensure their wellbeing and safety.<br />\n<br />\nThere are four requests that we ask that you consider raising with your counterparts in Beijing.<br />\n<br />\nThese are:<br />\n- That the young people be returned immediately to Hong Kong. If they are to stand trial, they should be tried in the Hong Kong courts,<br />\n- That the activists be allowed to nominate the legal representatives chosen by their families,<br />\n- That the families of those arrested be allowed to contact them,<br />\n- That the activists be allowed access to their prescribed medication.<br />\n<br />\nWe hope that you will make addressing these concerns an urgent priority.<br />\n<br />\n更多詳情 MORE DETAILS:<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.hongkongwatch.org/all-posts/2020/12/1/new-155-parliamentarians-from-18-countries-publish-open-letter-to-carrie-lam-on-case-of-12-hk-youths-100-days-after-they-were-detained-in-shenzhen?fbclid=IwAR2sImCDq5XInxmmcZW4fCCMm6N-wvJ7QaTdPMrwornsHspNuZOXbbkIN-U\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hongkongwatch.org%2Fall-posts%2F2020%2F12%2F1%2Fnew-155-parliamentarians-from-18-countries-publish-open-letter-to-carrie-lam-on-case-of-12-hk-youths-100-days-after-they-were-detained-in-shenzhen%3Ffbclid%3DIwAR2sImCDq5XInxmmcZW4fCCMm6N-wvJ7QaTdPMrwornsHspNuZOXbbkIN-U&d=TN93oS71akEChVkkxtef2SlZyh30VB0jKt3ffwT98zY%3D&h=252629fa\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.hongkongwatch.org/all-posts/2020/12/1/new-155-parliamentarians-from-18-countries-publish-open-letter-to-carrie-lam-on-case-of-12-hk-youths-100-days-after-they-were-detained-in-shenzhen?fbclid=IwAR2sImCDq5XInxmmcZW4fCCMm6N-wvJ7QaTdPMrwornsHspNuZOXbbkIN-U</a><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/HongKongWatch1/photos/a.1478139028973232/3421395874647528/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FHongKongWatch1%2Fphotos%2Fa.1478139028973232%2F3421395874647528%2F&d=TN93oS71akEChVkkxtef2SlZyh30VB0jKt3ffwT98zY%3D&h=282ec2f5\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/HongKongWatch1/photos/a.1478139028973232/3421395874647528/</a>"},{"pid":"98bb621f0c6665631c7b73d866b5665b9c3f378c","tid":2308086,"uid":240362,"like":9,"dislike":1,"score":8,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-01T15:15:56.000Z","msg":"<strong><span class=\"red\">NE